text: Quasilinear may refer to: * Quasilinear function, a function that is both quasiconvex and quasiconcave * Quasilinear utility, an economic utility function linear in one argument * In complexity theory and mathematics, O(n log n) or sometimes O(n (log n)k) * Quasilinear equation, a type of differential equation where the coefficient of the highest order derivative does not depend on the derivative of the unknown function
title: Quasilinear
